Maybe I'm not that kid who hacked and coded on Commodore systems but I played bunch of NES, SNES and SEGA games. I miss those days and I decided why not creating the most authentic retro gaming experience on NixOS using retroarch and shaders? the following is my opinions about what is "the best". I promise you a very high quality retro gaming experience once you do all those things.

first off here are my recommended cores for **best accuracy and performance**

``` nix
systemPackages = with pkgs; [
  (stable.retroarch.withCores (cores: with cores; [
    mesen              # nes
    snes9x             # snes
    beetle-psx-hw      # ps1
    pcsx2              # ps2
    fbneo              # arcade (MAME)
    mgba               # gba
    genesis-plus-gx    # sega genesis/megadrive
    sameboy            # gb + gbc
    mupen64plus        # n64
    melonds            # nds
  ]))
];
```

## what games stand out for each system

according to claude

> 🎮 NES mesen Platformers: Super Mario Bros. 3, Mega Man 2, Castlevania III Action/Adventure: The Legend of Zelda, Metroid, Contra Honorable mentions: Ninja Gaiden II, DuckTales, Kirby's Adventure
>
> 🎮 SNES snes9x Platformers: Super Mario World, Mega Man X, Donkey Kong Country 2 RPG: Final Fantasy VI — if you've never played it, you truly owe it to yourself; one of the best in the series or any series. Chrono Trigger, Secret of Mana, EarthBound Action: Super Metroid, A Link to the Past, Contra III Honorable mentions: Chrono Trigger's compact time-traveling adventure became a gold standard that stands up to many AAA RPG experiences on modern consoles today. F-Zero, Street Fighter II Turbo steamcommunityGitHub
>
> 🎮 Mega Drive genesis-plus-gx Platformers: Sonic the Hedgehog 2, Sonic 3 & Knuckles, Aladdin Action/Beat-em-up: Streets of Rage 2, Gunstar Heroes, Comix Zone RPG: Phantasy Star IV, Shining Force II Honorable mentions: Castlevania Bloodlines, Thunder Force IV, ToeJam & Earl
>
> 🎮 Game Boy / GBC sameboy Platformers: Kirby's Dream Land 2, Wario Land 3, Metroid II RPG: Pokémon Gold/Silver, The Legend of Zelda: Link's Awakening DX Honorable mentions: Metal Gear Solid (GBC), Shantae
>
> 🎮 GBA mgba Platformers: Castlevania: Aria of Sorrow, Mega Man Zero 2, Metroid Fusion RPG: Final Fantasy VI Advance, Golden Sun, Mother 3, Pokémon Emerald Action: The Legend of Zelda: Minish Cap, Advance Wars Honorable mentions: Fire Emblem, Kirby & The Amazing Mirror, Tactics Ogre
>
> 🎮 N64 mupen64plus 3D Platformers: Super Mario 64, Banjo-Kazooie, Donkey Kong 64 Adventure: Ocarina of Time at \#1, Majora's Mask at \#3 — non-negotiable. Shooter: GoldenEye 007, Perfect Dark Racing: Mario Kart 64, F-Zero X Honorable mentions: Paper Mario, Conker's Bad Fur Day, Star Fox 64 GitHub
>
> 🎮 PS1 beetle-psx-hw RPG: Final Fantasy VII, VIII, IX, Chrono Cross, Vagrant Story, Suikoden II Action/Adventure: Castlevania: Symphony of the Night, Metal Gear Solid, Crash Bandicoot 2 Racing: Gran Turismo 2 Honorable mentions: Spyro 2, Resident Evil 2, Tony Hawk's Pro Skater 2
>
> 🎮 NDS melonds RPG: Pokémon HeartGold/SoulSilver, Final Fantasy Tactics A2, Radiant Historia Action/Adventure: Castlevania: Dawn of Sorrow, The World Ends With You, Zelda: Phantom Hourglass Visual Novel: Ace Attorney series (all 3), Ghost Trick Honorable mentions: Dragon Quest IX, Chrono Trigger DS port (best version)
>
> 🎮 PS2 pcsx2 Action/Adventure: Shadow of the Colossus, God of War II, ICO, Okami Open World: GTA: San Andreas, GTA: Vice City RPG: Final Fantasy XII, Persona 3 & 4, Kingdom Hearts II, Dragon Quest VIII Platformers: Jak & Daxter, Ratchet & Clank 3, Sly Cooper 2 Honorable mentions: Burnout 3, Silent Hill 2, Devil May Cry 3

